com.github.rschmitt.collider

Class ClojureList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.rschmitt.collider.ClojureList<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>

    @Immutable
public class ClojureList<T>
extends Object
implements List<T>
    A generic persistent immutable List implementation, with three types of methods:
    1. Read methods from List, such as get(int)
    2. Write methods from List, such as add(T); these will throw UnsupportedOperationException
      3. and have been marked as @Deprecated
    3. Persistent "modification" methods, such as append(T); these will efficiently create modified copies of the current list
